<br>
<br>
Level 40 Epic Quest:<br>
<br>
Blessed Northern Axe (Warrior)<br>
DPS: 14.1<br>
SPD: 3.5<br>
QUA: 100%<br>
BON: 20%<br>
<br>
Barbed Claws (Savage)<br>
DPS: 13.7<br>
SPD: 3.2<br>
QUA: 100%<br>
BON: 20%<br>
<br>
<br>
- The Savage Small Shield Ability - Upon becoming a Savage, the<br>
player can no longer equip small shields. This either needs to be fixed, or<br>
the ability needs to be removed from the Savage.<br>
<br>
- Greave Style Trails Missing - When using a greave weapon, there<br>
are no style trails when styles are performed. Style trails are present<br>
for weapons held in the hands. They are not present for weapons the mount<br>
on the forearm.<br>
<br>
<br>
Suggestions:<br>
<br>
- Savages do not have the Prevent Flight RA - I believe this is an<br>
oversight, as the Savage needs the RA to assist in retaining enemies in<br>
melee range. The Savage has no other forms of CC and has no ranged damage.<br>
These are general criteria for a class deserving of Prevent Flight.<br>
<br>
- Kelgor's Recovery - To counter excessive downtime: The biggest<br>
problem with soloing a Savage in PvE is the downtime. Yellow-con mobs will<br>
often take the Savage down to 1/4 health, leaving a long rest before<br>
fighting again. Kelgor's Recovery would fix this; it would be a non-combat<br>
only ability that would slowly draw points from Endurance and increase the<br>
rate of HP regeneration. (Do not replace Kelgor's Boon with this ability,<br>
though. Kelgor's Boon should stay as it is.)<br>
<br>
- Remove Interruption from Taunt - The Taunt ability was added to<br>
the Savagery line with the intent of giving the Savage a way to pull mobs<br>
in PvE. The interruption component of this ability was not a necessary<br>
component, and it is having an overpowering effect on the class. The<br>
interruption component is not a problem on Paladins or Friars because they<br>
are hybrid classes without the CC-prevention RAs of a pure tank. The<br>
Savage has cheaper Purge and Determination to allow them to get through<br>
caster CC, and the instant interruption ability is simply an added nail in<br>
the caster coffin in this scenario. Removing the interruption component<br>
from the Savage only will make the encounter more balanced.<br>
<br>
- Ravager Replacement - Ravager has not functioned properly since<br>
day one. In fact, messaging is still printing as a cut/paste of the Void<br>
style. The style is completely worthless, as our normal styles do the same<br>
amount of damage without the penalty of a re-use timer. Remove the Ravager<br>
style from the RA list and replace it with Sense Aggression.<br>
<br>
Sense Aggression - an anti-stealth tool that taps the primal energy of the<br>
Savage to locate potential hidden attackers. Effect: The Savage can<br>
see/target the shadow-form of any stealther within the radius of effect.<br>
Radius: 350wu. Cost: The Savage spends HP to use this ability, draining HP<br>
while the ability is active at 1/2 rate sprinting drains Endurance.<br>
Constraints: The Savage must remain stationary for the ability to function,<br>
similar to a focus spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
II. Conclusion<br>
<br>
There are a couple minor bugs to address with the class. Beyond that,<br>
giving us Prevent Flight to assist with maintaining melee range with our<br>
RvR targets and Kelgor's Recovery to assist with our downtime issues in PvE<br>
will really flesh out the class.<br>
<br>
So to sum up... these are the things that Savages really need.<br>
<br>
<br>
Bugs<br>
<br>
1. Savages retain the Small Shields ability, but cannot equip the shields -<br>
just remove the ability to remove confusion.<br>
2. Pets Immune to Multi-Target Styles.<br>
3. Kelgor's Reward line - graphic not displaying in SI client by Kelgor's<br>
Boon or Kelgor's Gift.<br>
4. There are no style &quot;trails&quot; left by the greave-type weapons that mount<br>
on the wrist. Claw-type and fang-type weapons do leave style-trails.<br>
<br>
<br>
Suggestions<br>
<br>
1. Kelgor's Recovery<br>
2. Add Prevent Flight to the Savage RA List.<br>
3. Adjust quest rewards for Savages to be comparable in worth to other<br>
classes.<br>
4. Remove the interruption component from the Savage version of the<br>
instant-Taunt ability.<br>
5. Replace Ravager with Sense Aggression.<br>
